# 2.Problem 2. Add / Swap / ShiftLeft / Right in List (Unit Testing)

You are given the following **JavaScript code** :

| list-add-swap-shift-left-right.js |
| --- |
| **function** _createList_() {
     **let** data = [];
     **return** {
        add: **function** (item) {
            data.push(item)
        },
        shiftLeft: **function** () {
             **if** (data. **length** &gt; 1) {
                 **let** first = data.shift();
                data.push(first);
            }
        },
        shiftRight: **function** () {
             **if** (data. **length** &gt; 1) {
                 **let** last = data.pop();
                data.unshift(last);
            }
        },
        swap: **function** (index1, index2) {
             **if** (! **Number**.isInteger(index1) || index1 &lt; 0 || index1 &gt;= data. **length** ||
                ! **Number**.isInteger(index2) || index2 &lt; 0 || index2 &gt;= data. **length** ||
                index1 === index2) {
                 **return false** ;
            }
             **let** temp = data[index1];
            data[index1] = data[index2];
            data[index2] = temp;
             **return true** ;
        },
        toString: **function** () {
             **return** data.join( **&quot;, &quot;** );
        }
    };
} |

### Functionality

The above code creates a **list** data structure that holds items (of any type). It supports the following operations:

- **add(item)** â€“ **appends** given item to the end of the list.
- **shiftLeft()** â€“ shifts all elements **one position left** and the first elements comes last (with **rotation** ).
- **shiftRight()** â€“ shifts all elements **one position right** and the last elements comes first (with **rotation** ).
- **swap(index1, index2)** â€“ swaps the items at the specified indexes and returns **true**. If any of the two indexes **does not exist** or they are **equal** the collection stays **unchanged** and the method returns **false**.
- **toString()** â€“ returns the string representations of the **list items** , separated by &quot; **,**&quot;.

### Examples

This is an example how this code is **intended to be used** :

| Sample code usage |   | Corresponding output |

**list**.add(1);
**list**.add( **&quot;two&quot;** );
**list**.add(3);
**console**.log(**`list = [**${ **list** }**]`**);
**list**.shiftLeft();
**console**.log( **&quot;shifted left &lt;--&quot;** );
**console**.log(**`list = [**${ **list** }**]`**);
**list**.add([**&quot;four&quot;**]);
